    "body": "\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nWhen I'm trying to Reformat code with context menu and select `Reformat code` or `Reformat code with dartfmt` text is formatted totally ignoring `Hard wrap at` option in `Code Style`. It is true for both cases when EditorConfig support is enabled or not.\r\n\r\nAlso line wrap setting is ignored when I set `Format code on save` option on Flutter settings page and then save changed file.  \r\n\r\nExpected behavior is to call `flutter format $FILE -l 120` for example, when 'Hard wrap at' in 'Code Style'  is set to 120\r\n\r\n\r\n## Version info\r\n\r\nI don't know why flutter doctor don't know about Android Studio Dart and Flutter plugins version, but believe in Studio all needed is installed and working fine:\r\nFlutter plugin version is: 52.2.1\r\nDart plugin version is: 201.9317\r\n\r\nflutter doctor output:\r\n\r\n[âœ“] Flutter (Channel dev, 1.26.0-12.0.pre, on macOS 11.1 20C69 darwin-x64, locale en-US)\r\n    â€¢ Flutter version 1.26.0-12.0.pre at /Users/Shared/google/flutter/flutter-dev\r\n    â€¢ Framework revision a706cd2112 (13 days ago), 2021-01-14 18:20:26 -0500\r\n    â€¢ Engine revision effb529ece\r\n    â€¢ Dart version 2.12.0 (build 2.12.0-224.0.dev)\r\n\r\n[âœ“] Android toolchain - develop for Android devices (Android SDK version 30.0.3)\r\n    â€¢ Android SDK at /Users/Shared/android/sdk\r\n    â€¢ Platform android-30, build-tools 30.0.3\r\n    â€¢ ANDROID_HOME = /Users/Shared/android/sdk\r\n    â€¢ Java binary at: /Applications/Android Studio.app/Contents/jre/jdk/Contents/Home/bin/java\r\n    â€¢ Java version OpenJDK Runtime Environment (build 1.8.0_242-release-1644-b3-6915495)\r\n    â€¢ All Android licenses accepted.\r\n\r\n[âœ“] Xcode - develop for iOS and macOS\r\n    â€¢ Xcode at /Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer\r\n    â€¢ Xcode 12.3, Build version 12C33\r\n    â€¢ CocoaPods version 1.10.0\r\n\r\n[âœ“] Chrome - develop for the web\r\n    â€¢ Chrome at /Applications/Google Chrome.app/Contents